               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-197-person1760">
                  JOHN 
                  NOBBS
               <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1760" type="surname" value="NOBBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1760" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1760" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. 
               <persName id="t18300415-197-person1761">
                  Robert 
                  Pite
               <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1761" type="surname" value="Pite"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1761" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1761" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came in as a customer, and was there for twenty minutes, but bought nothing; the ribbons were in a drawer on the counter - I saw Mr. Pite take this ribbon from the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. What is the reason Mr. Pite is not here? A. I do not know - he was not before the Magistrate; I do not suppose there were three words spoken which I did not hear - Mr. Pite did not say he had hung a man once for robbing him, and he would hang this girl if he could; I observed the prisoner appeared silly - I have not heard that she is so.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-197-person1762">
                  JOHN 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1762" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1762" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-person1762" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took up the prisoner - I found nothing on her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to ask for some ribbon - he gave it me, and the man came and shoved this under my arm; the officer took it from me - I laid 1s. on the counter.</p>
               <p>Two witnesses gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-197-verdict1101" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-197-verdict1101" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
